go lanks durirg loading and carriage of crude oil cargoes must be clearly indicated in the Cargo Control Room: The Inspector will also verily the records of past cargo operations, lank pressures and other records al different slages of the cargo-handling operations and voyage required t0 be mainlained by the VOC Management Plan: He will further review the cargo plan ad deck logbook for the ongoing operations verify Inal requirernents of the VOC Managerriert Plan applicable t0 those specilic operalions had been incorporaled', '', 'KPI 10.1.3 requires thal VOC management procedures minimise marine and almospheric ernissions ard ensure that they are alwavs within permilted levels', 'Ship Specific VOC Target operating pressure can be found in VOC_ Seafarers" Practical Guide to SIRE 2.0 Inspections 25 Plans and during Flag during and');
