 andlor reporling of ship dala with regard t0 annual fuel oil consumplion, dislance travelled, hours underway and olher dala required by regulation 22A ol MARPOL Annex VI to the Flag Adninistralion. Records of fuel consuriplion must indude all the fuel oil consured on board, regardless of whelher the ship was underway Or nol: by lhe rain engines, auxiliary engines Lurbines, boilers and inert gas generalor; if lilled, and any other fuel consumer for each Lype of fuel oil consumed e.g. HFO, DO, LNG elc', '', 'KPI 10.1.1 requires thal an environmental proleclion policy and management plan on energy management and elficiency is in place: The policy; which is signed by senior managerrienl, includes commilrent t0 minimising the environmenlal impact of operalions. The policy is conspicuously posted onboard vessels and in company ollices ashore. All company personnel including third-party contractors are aware and familiar with the policy:', 'SEEMP part I-II-Il Documentary evidence that the package of measures as listed in SEEMP Part to improve the ship''s energy efficiency; had been implemented andlor monitored_ Measures should include improved voyage planning; weather routeing, just-in-time arrival, speed optimization, optimum trim, optimum use of auto-pilot rudder and heading systems, hull maintenance can be found in SEEMP part chapter 3.1');
