ents and sea service records (for lirne in rank only). All Senior Oflicers, junior deck Ollicers and cargo/gas Ergineers hold certificate in advanced training for oil, chemical or liquified gas tanker operations as applicable t0 the vessel lype: All junior Engineer Officers fiold & certificate in basic training for oil, chemical or liquified gas tanker operations as applicable t0 the vessel type. vessel operalor musl have developed procedures t0 ensure Inal: Each crew member is in possession ol all statutory and company mandatory certification ad course completion certificates required for their role onboard. Cerlilicalion for each individual is presented in & standard order wilh a index indicaling which cerlificales were manda for te role onboard. A consolidaled record of sea service is available for each olficer Make sure Ihal lhe sea lime in rank for all Officers iS accurale and records I0 verily sea lime in rank are available. (Verificalion checks will only cover up t0 36 months'' sea service onboard ) The endorsement for ary individual Ollicer muSL rellect tne delails of the national CoC on which Ihey are based OCIMF interprets & "person with immediate responsibility t0 include all walchkeeping Officers in charge of cargo-related operalions whether the vessel 15 at sea Or in port This includes the Znd Officer; 3rd Officer; 4th Officer ard GasiCargo Engineer It iay also include the purnprnan and olher Ratings ergaged in direct supervisior of cargo operations These crew members should have advariced training for oil, chernical or liquified gas lanker cargo operations applicable t0 lhe lype of vessel served on. Where Ralings, including lhe purpman, are assigned dulies wilh direct supervision of cargo operalions, the Inspector will verily thal lhey hold & cerlilicale in advanced training for oil, cemical 0r liquilied gas lanker operalions as applicable l0 the vessel lype .', '', 'KPI 3.2.3 requires thal tne company verifies Lhal vessel personnel qualily requirement