nsit of straits or inland waterways wilh considerable slandby requirements such as Singaporel Malacca Strails, Turkish Strails, English ChannelDover Strails Or similar: Post dry-dock departure and preparalions t0 relurn l0 commercial service: Navigalion during extended periods of restricted visibility. Exlensive tank cleaning operations. Extensive enclosed space operations- Periods of drills as recorded in the logbook. These should be marked correclly as working hours. Sealarers who are on call during & norinal rest period (for example, when responding to an engine-room alarm during a period when lhe engine-room iS unmanned) , Or are required t0 engage wilh unscheduled WOIk , received adequale compensalory rest period. The cornpensalory rest period should be added t0 lhe rest period t0 achieve lhe minirnum rest hours required pefore the sealarer returns t0 work personnel should record Ihe lime spent underlaking rounds Or responding alarins, recognising Ihal & non-conformance because ol such a response may be inevilable: The Inspector will also review the hours of rest record summary report provided t0 shore management and verify thal the management had acknowledged receipt and responded with an action plan where significant non-conformities were present in lhe surnmary report', '', 'KPI 34.1.3 requires thal procedures ensure lhal working and rest hours of all personnel are in line wilh the STCW, applicable Flag Slate requirements Or any relevant aulhorily guidelines for the vessel trade and are being accuralely recorded and monitored.', 'HSSE MANUAL 5.7.');
