in the first two weeks onboard. For NavigalionDeck Ollicers familiarisation with the navigational equipment fitted onboard the vessel to taking over navigational watch: familiarisation wilh lhe vessels cargo, ballast and mooring equipment before taking over a cargo watch For Engineer Officers familiarisation with the main propulsion, manoeuvring; cargo and ballast management and power generating equipment lilled onboard lhe vessel prior to undertaking scheduled duties. For specalist Officers familiarisation with the specialist equipment under lheir responsibility For conbractors familiarisation completed before any work was Carried oul onboard_ If the Companys SMS requires a familiarisa of the auditor performing sailing audits, the Inspector will verily compliarice', '', 'KPI 3.1.4 requires Ihal formal (arniliarisalion procedures are in place for vessel personnel, including conlractors', 'CP 8 covers the above requirements HSSE manual Chapter 6.0 TSM chanter Rnarding nf visitors and familv memhers Seafarers'' Practical Guide to SIRE 2.0 Inspections key prior prior lion');
