ual and fire safely operalional booklel mnay be cornbined ) The fire training manual, fire salely operalional booklet or life-saving manual must be provided in each crew mess room and recreation room, or in each crew cabin: The Inspector will review lhe records of onboard training and inslruclion for lhe LSA & FFA and verify Ihal training and instructions are provided (0 lhe crew for each item of FFA & LSA lisled within lwo weeks ol joining lhe vessel and then al intervals not exceeding two months lherealler Where lhe vessel is provided wilh & davit-launched life raft; lhie Inspeclor will review lhe instruclions for delivering lhe required onboard training and instruction, paying allention l0 any guidance on lhe use of training life raft (which must be conspicuously marked as such), where carried The Inspector will review the records of onboard training and instruction and verily Ihal training ad instruction in the use of the davit-launched life rafts where carried, had been undertaken wilhin the previous four months_', '', 'KPI 3.1.4 requires that formal familiarisation procedures are in place for vessel personnel, including contracors', 'SOLAS LSAIFFE training manuals The Inspector will review the records of onboard training and instruction for the LSA & FFA and verify that training and instructions are provided to the crew for each item of FFA & LSA listed within two weeks of joining the vessel and then at intervals not exceeding two months thereafter F.6.5 & Shipboard contingency plan 8.1.3 item No 8');
