e Master and Deck Oflicers_', '', 'KPI 3.1.4 requires that formal fariliarisation procedures are place for vessel personnel, including conliaclors', 'Timescale for the familiarization FNAV.24 mentions "within 24 hours from embarkation and prior assuming dutiesluse the ECDIS in a navigational watch Fresh familiarization is required for the Master and all the Bridge Officers, after any ECDIS software update prior use the ECDIS in navigational watch Method of familiarisation with the ECDIS equipment NPM chapter 6.14.1.3 Location of the familiarisation, on board or ashore-NPM chapter 6.14.1.3 & CP 7 chapter 3 Identity of the appropriately trained crew or training personnel authorised t0 deliver the familiarisation CP 8 chapter 3.2 & 4 Means of demonstrating competency upon completion of the familiarization and before taking charge of a navigational watch_ FNAV24 ''Upon completion of familiarization process, the Master must verify the competency level of subject officer; by demonstrating relevant ECDIS features" Seafarers" Practical Guide to SIRE 2.0 Inspections 55 al');
