peclion questionnaire The Inspector will review the ECDIS checklists and quick reference 45 well &5 records which deronstrale thal software updates had been compleled in accordance wilh manulacturer s instructions. Records l0 demonstrale periodic tests required by lhe manulacturer $ inslruclions must be compleled. Records which demonstrate lhal the ECDIS settings had been checked periodically during each voyage musL be available: The Inspector will raise a negalive observalion il there iS evidence Ihal ECDIS sellings had been incorreclly entered al ay slage ol voyage and if lhere is nO indicalion in lhe passage plan regarding required changes t0 ECDIS sellings. INTERTANKO''S Guide to Safe Navigation (including ECDIS) is available on the INTERTANKO website.', 'An Inspector will raise & negalive observalion if: An ECDIS unil is deleclive in any respecL The second ECDIS, where required t0 be fitted, was nol set Up aS a backup unil', 'KPI 5.1.2 requires Ihal comprehensive procedures L0 ensure sale navigalion are in place. These procedures Iray include electronic aids L0 ravigalion including ARPA, AIS and ECDIS:', 'Display management NPM 3.2.1 Alarms & warnings NPM 3.11.9 Settina safetv contours and depths as appropriate t0 the drauaht of the vessel NPM 3.6.2');
