e management are in place procedures may include use ol BNWAS.', 'When the BNWAS is required to be in operation NPM Chapter 6.4 The BNWAS in On" mode at all times (underway; at sea, drifting and at anchor) including when the ship s heading or track control system is in use, except when the ship is alongside, in dry-dock or at a repair facility: Who will activate the BNWAS and the process for so. NPM 6.4.1 the Master may set the system "On" or "Off" The bridge team members must not alter any settings without Master $ approval How the system will be protected from unauthorised deactivation_ What to do if a BNWAS stage 2 or 3 alarm is activated. The periodic tests and checks required to verify correct functioning of the BNWAS NPM 6.4 "The means of selecting the operational mode and the duration of the dormant period (Td) must be security protected so that access to these controls (key or password) must be exclusively restricted to the Master only');
