', 'The Inspector will raise a negalive observalion if: A GNSS receiver is deleclive in any respecL The posilional dala provided t0 anolher piece ol navigalion Or cormunicalion equiprent such as AIS, ARPA 0r a Global Marilire Dislress Salely Syslem lransceiver iS erroneous', 'KPI 5.1.2 requires Ihal comprehensive procedures L0 ensure sale navigalion are in place. These procedures rnay include electronic aids L0 navigalion including ARPA, AlS and ECDIS.', 'The configuration of the equipment NPM 6.12 The periodic checks and performance tests t0 be conducted NPM 6.12 Where more than one receiver is fitted, the process to switch the output from one receiver to another NPM 6.12 The periodic checks to verify that all equipment is receiving an accurate positional input NPM 6.12 The actions to take in the event of a single GNSS receiver failure The actions to take in the event of multiple GNSS receiver failures NPM 6.12 "It must be appreciated that any failure of the GNSS system will materially impact the navigation of the ship. In particular; ECDIS is optimized for positional input from the GNSS signal. In the event of a general GNSS failure , it will be necessary to operate the ECDIS in DRIEP mode, using traditional methods In the event of a GNSS system failure in restricted waters, consideration must be qiven t0 reducing speed to allow more time for Seafarers" Practical Guide to SIRE 2.0 Inspections Mlll and fixing');
