pared t0 water of & known depth', 'The echo sourder Or recording device musl nol be deleclive in any respecl', 'KPI 5.1.2 requires thal comprehensive procedures t0 ensure safe navigalion are in place. These procedures may include electronic aids t0 navigation including ARPA, AIS and ECDIS:', 'When the echo sounder is required t0 be in operation NPM 6.5 Where forward and aft transducers are fitted t0 the vessel, considerations for the set up and display of information_ When the echo sounder recording device is required to be operational and timelposition marking necessary: NPM 6.5. Where a separate printer is provided, the times the printer is required ''to be recording NPM 6.5 The criteria for the setting of the depth alarm where fitted NPM 6.5 "Whenever an echo sounder is equipped with a shallow water alarm, this alarm must be set to an appropriate safe depth to give a timely warning of approaching shallow water The minimum alarm value for the echo sounder must not on any occasion; be set to be less than the required Company''s under keel clearance at the corresponding area The requirements for periodic checks to confirm the proper functioning and accuracy of the echo sounder when compared to water of a known depth NPM 6.5 "At anchor; use a sounding lead to verify the proper operation of the echo sounder and depth readings on the chart Records shall be kept in the form of FNAV.23');
