ventory of spare navigational lamps identifying the luminosity Or wallage and the lion lights t0 which inay be lilled He will verily thal tne navigalion lights and navigalion light controller had been tested:', 'The navigation lighls or navigalion light controller should not be defeclive in any respect Navigation lights or their screens should not be damaged, relocated or obscured in such & way that the required spacing andlor arc of visibilily of any lights is apparenlly no longer in compliance with COLREG Annex requiremenls The required navigalional shapes musl be onboard ad in usable condition:', 'KPI 5.1.4 requires thal the company has procedures thal ensure all navigalional equipment is mainlained operalional.', 'Primary and secondary navigation lights are fully operational NPM 6.7 ,FNAV.12 PMS Primary and secondary power supplies to the navigational light controller are operational PMS Navigation Lines/Lighting [inspection]" Power supply failure alarm is operational PMS Navigation Lines/Lighting [inspection]" Where LED lamps are fitted, are within their usable lifespan for luminous intensity: This maybe achieved by integrated luminous intensity or usage monitoring systems with alarms Or by manual recording of usage Company''s vessels are not supplied with LED navigational lights Ref VMAInews Required navigational shapes are onboard and in good condition (three balls, one cylinder & one diamond) NPM 4.3.4 Liahts. shapes and sound sianals');
