set:', 'KPI 5.1.2 requires thal comprehensive procedures l0 ensure sale navigalion are in place', 'Standard magnetic, gyro and GNSS compasses carried onboard are properly maintained and serviced PMS & NPM Ch 6.6 Heading information for each compass is frequently checked through terrestrial, celestial andlor comparative observation NPM Ch 6.6 Frequent checks are made for heading accuracy output to all navigational equipment NPM Ch 6.6 (hourly) A record of error for each compass is maintained NPM Ch 6.6 An up-to-date deviation card is available on the bridge for the standard magnetic compass ~NPM Ch 6.6 The standard magnetic compass is adjusted when: the deviation consistently exceeds a defined value becomes unreliable, suffers damage , NPM Ch 6.6 records of compass error have not been maintained over the preceding two years NPM Ch 6.');
