 of periodic inspections and tests of Ine equipmenl', 'The Survival craft portable twO-way VHF radios should not be defective in any respecl; A survival crafl porlable (wO-way VHF radio should have & wrist or neck strap wilh a weak link, and should have provision for attachment to clothing: The seal of replaceable primary radio inuSI De inlacL Survival crall porlable lwo-way VHF radios Or replaceable primary balleries should be of a highly visible yellowlorange colour or marking:', 'KPI 9A.1.1 requires Ihal salely inspeclions are corducled al scheduled intervals by designated Salely Officer Salely inspeclions of the ship include all accessible areas of the ship.', 'The vessel operator must have developed a procedure to ensure that survival craft portable two-way VHF radios are periodically inspected and tested and ready for immediate use in an emergency: PMS Radio Log Procedures must also provide guidance on the use of the radios for non-emergency communications Shipboard contingency plan Chapter 9.1.16 (Portable two-ways VHF radiotelephone must not be used for normal radio Communication onboard the vessels; they are not intrinsically safe and must be used after abandoning the vessel:)');
