n mobile phones and porlable electronic equipmenl Briefing on Ihe hazards ol Ihe Cargo and any operalions place eg: loading; lank-cleanirg or gas-freeing: The use ol appropriale PPE while onboard:. Emergency signals actions in the case of an emergency: Drug and alcohol policy: During lhe course of the inspection, the Inspector will observe lhe arrangements for regular patrols of the deck to monitor potential unauthorised access points eg. hawse pipes, mooring ropes elc. When boarding the vessel, the Inspeclor will observe Ihe security arrangernents and induction and familiarisation procedures for visilors.', 'The Master musl provide the terminal with a list of approved visitors, indluding Agents, Surveyors, Loading Maslers and Ihe SIRE Inspector Where CCTV systems are provided, CCTV coverage of the vessel access points must be monitored', 'A notice board muSL be provided al lhe access L0 lhe vessel displaying the appropriale warnings l0 visitors, including lhe parlicular risks from toxic Or hazardous cargoes being handled ard the operalions taking place.', 'KPI 13.1.3 requires lhal measures have been developed l0 miligale and respond t0 all identified threals l0 vessels and shore-based localions;', 'Visitor induction and familiarisation TSM 1.7 Boarding of visitors and family members TSM 11.10 Boarding and monitoring of visitors form F 16.52 Pre-approval of visitors for terminal security purposes FISPS.23 security pre-arrival checklist');
