INSERT INTO ecdis_procedures (paragraph_number, question, question_category, piq, photograph, question_type, objective, roviq_sequence, tagged_rank, verification_by, human_requirements, process_requirements, hardware_requirements, tmsa_requirements, comments_sms_reference) VALUES ('', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'During lhe tour ol the vessel, the Inspector inspect equipment I0 verily physical cyber security measures are in place: Space conlaining sensitive IT or OT control equipment must be securely locked. Physical access l0 sensitive user equipment (such as exposed USB ports on bridge systems) must be secured or disabled. USB hubs should nol be used unless they are properly conkrolled. Back-up facilities musl be available ad used. On-board compulers must be protected by anti-virus software Anti-virus software must be regularly updated Application software musl be regularly updaled wilh upgrades and security patches Senior Officer musl have an administrator profile User profiles rusl be allowed compuler workslalions l0 be used only for their interided purpose User profiles must be actively managed: Generic user profiles and passwords must nol be passed on at crew changes Usernames and passwords must not be posted at workstations Common User Profiles (instead of Super User) should be activated for Auxiliary Boilers control station: The key for aclivalion ol ECR alarms olf-scan mode should be in possession ol Chiel Erigineer', 'KPI 13.1.2 requires that the company has documented procedures in place t0 identify security threats applicable t0 vessels trading areas and shore-based localions', 'Identified the roles and responsibilities of users, personnel, and management both ashore and on board, including: 0 The officer with responsibility for cyber risk management on board. IT systems & Cyber security manual chapter ''Terms & definitions IT Manager & IT Administrator: 0 The person responsible for managing user profiles and passwords in the vessel network In section 9.3 (page 12) it is clearly noted that Manager & IT Administrators are responsible for managing user profiles and passwords in the vessel''s network along with the password reset privilege by the captain: Identified the IT(information technology) and OT(operational technology) systems at risk on board such as: Cargo management systems_ Bridge systems Propulsion and machinery management and power control systems Access control systems 0 Administrative and crew welfare systems_ Communication systems The above requirements are covered by the ship-specific IT-OT inventory located in VMA other materila ship_specific_it-ot inventory Described technical protection measures t0 protect against a cyber incident such as Physical security of network components Use of media lockers as described in chapter 18 Access for visitors" 0 Anti-virus software Chapter 14.6 PROTECTION AGAINST MALICIOUS SOFTWARE Application software management Chapter 13.2 "INFRASTRUCTURE SOFTWARE Back-up facilities Chapter 13.7 BACKUPS Control of crew internet access Chapter 13.4" INFRASTRUCTURE - ACCEPTABLE INTERNET USAGE" & TSM ch 1.5 & NPM ch 4.3.4.10.2');
